                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add-protein: top with grilled chicken, halloumi, or a soft-boiled egg for a main-course salad.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Crunch upgrade: scatter toasted nuts or seeds on top, pumpkin, almond, sunflower.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Designed as a make-ahead: assemble the night before, eat in the morning.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Chinese home cooking favours bright contrast: salt, sweet, sour, heat, working against each other in one bowl. The dish lands somewhere on that grid, adjust the balance to suit your palate.",
